        <div class="story">
            <div class="story-title">China breaks 3D printing speed records</div>
            <div class="story-content">New DISH technology prints millimeter-scale objects in just 0.6 seconds, achieving 333 cubic mm/second rates and 12-micrometer precision. Potential for micro-components and mobile phone camera modules.</div>
            <a href="https://news.cgtn.com/news/2026-02-13/0-6-second-3D-printing-China-s-new-DISH-tech-shatters-records-1KJoOP49xHW/p.html" class="story-link">CGTN</a>
        </div>

        <div class="story">
            <div class="story-title">MIT makes aluminum 5x stronger using 3D printing</div>
            <div class="story-content">Opening new possibilities for aerospace and automotive applications.</div>
            <a href="https://www.sciencedaily.com/releases/2025/12/251226045316.htm" class="story-link">ScienceDaily</a>
        </div>

        <div class="story">
            <div class="story-title">3D printed custom batteries now possible</div>
            <div class="story-content">Filling oddly shaped spaces that would otherwise go to waste.</div>
            <a href="https://hackaday.com/2026/02/14/theres-always-room-for-3d-printed-batteries/" class="story-link">Hackaday</a>
        </div>

        <div class="story">
            <div class="story-title">Walmart taps 3D printing for building construction</div>
            <div class="story-content">Greeley-based Alquist 3D will print over a dozen Walmart buildings using leased A1X printers.</div>
            <a href="https://hoodline.com/2026/02/greeley-3d-printing-upstart-snags-walmart-building-spree/" class="story-link">Hoodline</a>
        </div>
